
Usage:

    {{#cyan}}bower{{/cyan}} install
    {{#cyan}}bower{{/cyan}} install <folder>
    {{#cyan}}bower{{/cyan}} install <pkg>
    {{#cyan}}bower{{/cyan}} install <pkg>#<version>

Options:

    {{#yellow}}--save{{/yellow}}         - Save installed packages into the project's {{{json}}} dependencies
    {{#yellow}}--save-dev{{/yellow}}     - Save installed packages into the project's {{{json}}} devDependencies
    {{#yellow}}--force{{/yellow}}        - Force fetching remote resources even if a local copy exists on disk
    {{#yellow}}--force-latest{{/yellow}} - Force latest version on conflict
    {{#yellow}}--production{{/yellow}}   - Do not install project devDependencies
    {{#yellow}}--no-color{{/yellow}}     - Do not print colors

Can specify one or more:

    {{#cyan}}bower{{/cyan}} install ./foo/package git://example.com#1.0.2

Description:

    Installs a browser package locally into a {{{directory}}} directory
